HEADWORD: Grego
<hw>Gre"go</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. fr, It. <ets>Greco</ets> Greek, or Sp.
<ets>Griego</ets>, or Pg. <ets>Grego</ets>.]</ety> <def>A short jacket
or cloak, made of very thick, coarse cloth, with a hood attached, worn
by the Greeks and others in the Levant.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>griego</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
